00:09:12,452 --> 00:09:14,886
Ooh!
           (chuckles)

261
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:16,154
Okay.

262
00:09:16,156 --> 00:09:19,491
I apologize.
        I'm just being thorough.

263
00:09:19,493 --> 00:09:21,293
Call me. Easy!

264
00:09:24,464 --> 00:09:26,498
(indistinct chatter)

265
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,999
CHLOE:
   What has gotten into you?

266
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:29,434
I thought you were getting
       the hang of this.

267
00:09:29,436 --> 00:09:30,802
LUCIFER:
  I got you a lead, didn't I?

268
00:09:30,804 --> 00:09:33,004
The ex-boyfriend,
you looking into him?

269
00:09:33,006 --> 00:09:34,839
Yeah, Dan's on it, but
           that's not the point.

270
00:09:34,841 --> 00:09:37,275
This whole new thing, you
      making out with witnesses?

271
00:09:37,277 --> 00:09:39,477
Completely inappropriate.

272
00:09:39,479 --> 00:09:41,580
When are you going to get it?
Inappropriate is what I do.

273
00:09:41,582 --> 00:09:42,981
You've always been
  a pain in the ass, Lucifer,

274
00:09:42,983 --> 00:09:45,317
but I've never
      seen you like this.

275
00:09:45,319 --> 00:09:47,452
What's going on?
         What happened?

276
00:09:47,454 --> 00:09:48,453
Just enough of the questioning,
Detective.

277
00:09:48,455 --> 00:09:50,188
Reprimand me
or let's get on with it.

278
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:51,189
(scoffs)

279
00:09:51,191 --> 00:09:52,223
DAN:
Wow.

280
00:09:52,225 --> 00:09:54,726
Can I talk to you, please?

281
00:09:54,728 --> 00:09:56,261
(groans)
             Pull your pants up.

282
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:57,262
Hi.

283
00:09:57,264 --> 00:09:58,413
Hey, what's up with him?

284
00:09:58,414 --> 00:09:59,563
Looks like he just rolled out
of bed or something.

285
00:09:59,566 --> 00:10:00,565
CHLOE:
I don't know.

286
00:10:00,567 --> 00:10:01,566
There's just something

287
00:10:01,568 --> 00:10:02,334
completely off
                about him today.

288
00:10:02,336 --> 00:10:03,335
Yeah, well, there's something's

289
00:10:03,337 --> 00:10:04,669
really off about him every day.

290
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:05,670
No, no, it's different.

291
00:10:05,672 --> 00:10:07,005
He's missing his usual...

292
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:08,873
extreme glee.

293
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:12,077
He-he just seems really dark.
Look, is he gonna be a problem?

294
00:10:12,079 --> 00:10:13,812
'Cause you know I wouldn't mind
if you send him home.

295
00:10:13,814 --> 00:10:14,813
Nope, not a problem.
You sure?

296
00:10:14,815 --> 00:10:16,081
Yep, got it.
                I can handle it.

297
00:10:16,083 --> 00:10:17,515
What'd you get from ballistics?

298
00:10:17,517 --> 00:10:18,650
I confirmed

299
00:10:18,652 --> 00:10:20,485
large caliber bullet
from a rifle; long-range.

300
00:10:20,487 --> 00:10:22,053
I have a team searching a wider
perimeter for more evidence.

301
00:10:22,055 --> 00:10:23,989
(door swings open)
And I finished

302
00:10:23,991 --> 00:10:25,890
the background check
on everyone at the wedding.

303
00:10:25,892 --> 00:10:27,459
All clean.

304
00:10:27,461 --> 00:10:28,860
But the ex-boyfriend,
Jason Myers, he's not.

305
00:10:28,862 --> 00:10:31,396
He's got one aggravated assault,
two weapons violations.

306
00:10:31,398 --> 00:10:33,231
I have him waiting in
interrogation for you.

307
00:10:44,311 --> 00:10:46,678
Well...

308
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:49,114
hello, bad guy.

309
00:10:49,116 --> 00:10:51,316
¶ ¶

310
00:10:58,158 --> 00:10:59,224
DAN: Lucifer,
             open the damn door!

311
00:10:59,226 --> 00:11:00,325
(banging on door)
                          CHLOE:
                        Lucifer!

312
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:03,395
Lucifer, open this
                 door right now!

313
00:11:03,397 --> 00:11:05,664
(sobbing)

314
00:11:08,468 --> 00:11:09,934
Lucifer, what
                  are you doing?

315
00:11:09,936 --> 00:11:10,935
(sighs)

316
00:11:10,937 --> 00:11:12,537
Just having a little
chitchat

317
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:13,805
with our friend here.

318
00:11:13,807 --> 00:11:15,573
Care to know
              what I've learned?

319
00:11:15,575 --> 00:11:17,709
You get out
                   of there now.

320
00:11:17,711 --> 00:11:20,879
Oh, she's so demanding.

321
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:28,820
Well... he's innocent.

322
00:11:28,822 --> 00:11:30,588
CHLOE: Oh, did you
figure that out

323
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:32,524
before or after
       you tortured him?

324
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:33,725
You tortured a suspect?

325
00:11:33,727 --> 00:11:35,493
I didn't lay a finger
on the spineless cretin.

326
00:11:35,495 --> 00:11:36,995
Come on, the guy's
  sitting on the floor crying.

327
00:11:36,997 --> 00:11:38,830
Crying because
of a woman,

328
00:11:38,832 --> 00:11:41,066
not me-- the bride,
to be specific.

329
00:11:41,068 --> 00:11:42,834
However, he did not
kill her.

330
00:11:42,836 --> 00:11:43,968
And you know that how?

331
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:45,670
He said he couldn't take
seeing the bride so happy,

332
00:11:45,672 --> 00:11:48,540
so he ran off, crying--
surprise, surprise--

333
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:50,842
well before
the shooting started.

334
00:11:50,844 --> 00:11:52,077
And you believed that?

335
00:11:52,079 --> 00:11:53,845
Of course not.
He had an alibi.
                         Really?

336
00:11:53,847 --> 00:11:56,114
Yes. Leaving the park
on the service road,

337
00:11:56,116 --> 00:11:58,083
he bumped into
a wedding musician.

338
00:11:58,085 --> 00:12:00,852
Didn't get a name, but he had
a buzz cut and a guitar case.

339
00:12:00,854 --> 00:12:03,188
A guitar? No.

340
00:12:03,190 --> 00:12:04,989
They booked a DJ,
                not a live band.

341
00:12:04,991 --> 00:12:07,525
Trust me, crying guy
isn't lying.

342
00:12:07,527 --> 00:12:10,428
Maybe, but maybe there wasn't
     a guitar in that case.

343
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:13,565
Oh, so you think our musician
might be the shooter.

344
00:12:13,567 --> 00:12:15,767
He's pretty shaken up,
         but he's gonna be okay.

345
00:12:15,769 --> 00:12:16,868
You're lucky.

346
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:18,670
Okay, I still have
     to question properly.

347
00:12:18,672 --> 00:12:21,272
But there's a possibility
  that Jason saw our shooter,

348
00:12:21,274 --> 00:12:23,808
and he may have been carrying
  his rifle in a guitar case.

349
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:25,844
Last seen
on the park service road.

350
00:12:25,846 --> 00:12:28,012
I'm on it.

351
00:12:30,617 --> 00:12:32,684
You're welcome.
                      Excuse me?

352
00:12:32,686 --> 00:12:34,886
What you just did in there
    is incredibly inappropriate.

353
00:12:34,888 --> 00:12:36,888
Are you trying

354
00:12:36,890 --> 00:12:37,889
to get in trouble
               or are you trying

355
00:12:37,891 --> 00:12:39,057
to piss me off?

356
00:12:39,059 --> 00:12:40,525
I did what I had to do.

357
00:12:40,527 --> 00:12:42,160
Got results, didn't I?

358
00:12:42,162 --> 00:12:43,928
If you pull one more
                stunt like that,

359
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:46,464
I don't care how
              effective you are,

360
00:12:46,466 --> 00:12:47,766
I will bench you.

361
00:13:05,452 --> 00:13:07,919
(single note resonates)

362
00:13:09,923 --> 00:13:12,390
I take it you heard about Uriel?

363
00:13:16,763 --> 00:13:18,730
Is Lucifer here?

364
00:13:18,732 --> 00:13:20,365
No, he's out.

365
00:13:20,367 --> 00:13:23,001
Probably in the middle
of some three-way,

366
00:13:23,003 --> 00:13:24,769
like nothing happened.

367
00:13:24,771 --> 00:13:27,338
Not everyone grieves
                   the same way.

368
00:13:27,340 --> 00:13:31,342
Lucifer, he's never
                  been one to...

369
00:13:31,344 --> 00:13:33,978
face his emotions.

370
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:37,215
Instead of looking in,
                    he acts out.

371
00:13:37,217 --> 00:13:39,584
You know,
               a rebellion here,

372
00:13:39,586 --> 00:13:42,253
an apple there?

373
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:44,789
But you...

374
00:13:44,791 --> 00:13:46,558
How are you doing?

375
00:13:48,728 --> 00:13:50,995
Come on, tell your mom.

376
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:53,832
When I first heard
of Uriel's death,

377
00:13:53,834 --> 00:13:55,099
I wanted to blame Lucifer.

378
00:13:55,101 --> 00:13:58,603
but... then I realized
I was just as much to blame,

379
00:13:58,605 --> 00:14:01,873
if not more.

380
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:02,974
None of this
      would have happened

381
00:14:02,976 --> 00:14:04,943
if I still had my...

382
00:14:04,945 --> 00:14:06,845
Your powers.

383
00:14:08,582 --> 00:14:09,747
How did you know?

384
00:14:09,749 --> 00:14:12,116
A mother knows.

385
00:14:15,689 --> 00:14:18,156
But I also know
                   it's possible

386
00:14:18,158 --> 00:14:21,960
to regain your strength.

387
00:14:21,962 --> 00:14:23,094
That we both can.

388
00:14:23,096 --> 00:14:25,463
No, Mom, it's too late.

389
00:14:25,465 --> 00:14:28,266
Uriel would...

390
00:14:28,268 --> 00:14:31,269
He would still be alive
if it wasn't for me.

391
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:37,342
Come, there's something
                you need to see.

392
00:14:45,418 --> 00:14:48,653
Okay, so we found something
          near the service road.

393
00:14:50,323 --> 00:14:52,223
Look at this.

394
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:56,027
It's a nice little hiding
        spot behind some bushes.

395
00:14:56,029 --> 00:14:57,528
Disturbed ground.

396
00:14:57,530 --> 00:14:58,997
Clear view of the stage.

397
00:14:58,999 --> 00:15:01,266
Someone with a rifle
        could've made this shot.

398
00:15:01,268 --> 00:15:02,834
What's that?

399
00:15:02,836 --> 00:15:04,035
That...

400
00:15:04,037 --> 00:15:05,803
is a pastry napkin
        from a Dutch food truck.

401
00:15:05,805 --> 00:15:08,206
"Freddy's Dutch Oven"?
            (sniffs)

402
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:10,575
Love this place.
       Unfortunate name,

403
00:15:10,577 --> 00:15:11,910
but best stroopwafel
         in Hollywood.

404
00:15:11,912 --> 00:15:13,912
The napkin is
          definitely from today.

405
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:15,213
The syrup is still
               wet to the touch.

406
00:15:15,215 --> 00:15:16,881
And undoubtedly tasty.

407
00:15:16,883 --> 00:15:19,584
So if the shooter bought this
stroop-- whatever you call it--

408
00:15:19,586 --> 00:15:21,886
with his credit card,
we can track his identity.

409
00:15:21,888 --> 00:15:23,087
So we need to
get to the food truck

410
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:24,522
and talk to the owner.

411
00:15:24,524 --> 00:15:25,523
I will put out a BOLO.

412
00:15:25,525 --> 00:15:27,158
What is it with you
and BOLOs?

413
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:28,792
Why don't you just use
Freddy's Dutch Oven app?

414
00:15:28,795 --> 00:15:30,328
Gives you their
current locale.

415
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:31,863
You never know
    when you're in the mood

416
00:15:31,865 --> 00:15:33,364
for a good strooping.

417
00:15:35,869 --> 00:15:39,637
¶ You better mount up ¶

418
00:15:39,639 --> 00:15:43,207
¶ You better ride on ¶

419
00:15:43,209 --> 00:15:46,611
¶ You better run ¶

420
00:15:46,613 --> 00:15:48,846
¶ Run away ¶

421
00:15:48,848 --> 00:15:50,815
¶ ¶

422
00:15:50,817 --> 00:15:52,050
You know what?

423
00:15:52,052 --> 00:15:53,318
You stay here.

424
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,553
Don't move.
            I'll do the talking.

425
00:15:55,555 --> 00:15:58,356
Fine by me.

426
00:15:58,358 --> 00:16:00,558
Detective Decker, LAPD.
Are you the owner?

427
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,094
Alfred Loomis, but
         you can call me Freddy.

428
00:16:03,096 --> 00:16:05,029
And let me guess.
         You look like

429
00:16:05,031 --> 00:16:06,564
a "chocolade hagelslag"
         kind of girl.

430
00:16:06,566 --> 00:16:07,565
Am I right?

431
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:08,766
Sir, earlier today
you served a man

432
00:16:08,768 --> 00:16:10,234
with a buzz cut, possibly
carrying a guitar case.

433
00:16:10,236 --> 00:16:11,469
Does that ring a bell?

434
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:14,706
If I may, one order
    of "oliebollen," please.

435
00:16:14,708 --> 00:16:15,974
What?

436
00:16:15,976 --> 00:16:17,008
Oliebollen.

437
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,609
Literally means
         "oily balls."

438
00:16:18,611 --> 00:16:20,478
Tastes better than it sounds,
          believe me.

439
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,981
Thank you.
     No, sorry, Detective,

440
00:16:22,983 --> 00:16:24,148
I don't remember
       anyone like that.

441
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,217
But I wasn't here
   during the morning shift.

442
00:16:26,219 --> 00:16:28,419
Um, Freddy, I forgot
                     to tell you

443
00:16:28,421 --> 00:16:30,521
a guy like that was
             here when I opened.

444
00:16:30,523 --> 00:16:33,024
He was asking when
                you'd be around.

445
00:16:33,026 --> 00:16:34,559
Asking for me specifically?

446
00:16:34,561 --> 00:16:36,427
Actually, you know what?
  Make the two orders, please.

447
00:16:36,429 --> 00:16:37,428
I'm famished.
  (impatient groans, murmurs)

448
00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:40,264
Lucifer--
           (gunshots)

449
00:16:40,266 --> 00:16:42,133
Everybody down!
       (panicked screams)

450
00:16:43,837 --> 00:16:46,637
(sirens approaching)

451
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:48,573
Shooter on the roof.
      Victim in the truck.

452
00:16:48,575 --> 00:16:49,640
Secure the scene!

453
00:16:50,777 --> 00:16:52,610
Bloody hell!

454
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:11,329
(seagulls cawing)

455
00:17:31,918 --> 00:17:34,652
(distant siren wailing)

456
00:17:34,654 --> 00:17:36,921
Not very polite
         of Mr. Shooter to leave

457
00:17:36,923 --> 00:17:38,322
without saying good-bye.

458
00:17:38,324 --> 00:17:40,425
His bullets are saying plenty.

459
00:17:40,427 --> 00:17:42,060
Well, why shoot
              Food Truck Freddy,

460
00:17:42,062 --> 00:17:43,461
just 'cause you were
                questioning him?

461
00:17:43,463 --> 00:17:46,464
No, this was premeditated.

462
00:17:46,466 --> 00:17:48,199
The shooter came here
to find him,

463
00:17:48,201 --> 00:17:49,534
then went to shoot the bride,

464
00:17:49,536 --> 00:17:51,803
then came back when
he knew Freddy would be here.

465
00:17:57,343 --> 00:17:59,510
This guy's got a list.

466
00:17:59,512 --> 00:18:00,812
God, who's next?

467
00:18:00,814 --> 00:18:03,681
(chuckles)
       <i> He's</i> not gonna tell you.

468
00:18:10,490 --> 00:18:12,590
Come bloody on!

469
00:18:12,592 --> 00:18:13,825
(sighs)

470
00:18:13,827 --> 00:18:15,660
(banging on machine)

471
00:18:16,763 --> 00:18:17,995
What are you doing?

472
00:18:17,997 --> 00:18:19,697
That's twice now today
I've been denied snacks.

473
00:18:19,699 --> 00:18:20,932
You got change
for a hundie?

474
00:18:20,934 --> 00:18:22,751
Oh, God.

475
00:18:22,752 --> 00:18:24,569
All right, ballistics confirmed
         the same rifle was used

476
00:18:24,571 --> 00:18:27,738
in both shootings, but no prints
      were found on the rooftop.

477
00:18:27,740 --> 00:18:29,107
This guy paid cash
              at the food truck.

478
00:18:29,109 --> 00:18:32,877
He really covers
                     his tracks.

479
00:18:32,879 --> 00:18:34,579
If I could just
       find a connection

480
00:18:34,581 --> 00:18:36,747
between our two victims.

481
00:18:36,749 --> 00:18:38,616
But Peggy Russo
and Freddy Loomis

482
00:18:38,618 --> 00:18:40,151
seem to have
nothing in common.

483
00:18:40,153 --> 00:18:41,719
LUCIFER:
     Apart from being dead.

484
00:18:41,721 --> 00:18:44,655
Uh, maybe they were
           just randomly chosen.

485
00:18:44,657 --> 00:18:45,823
Mm, my gut says no.

486
00:18:45,825 --> 00:18:47,492
This guy is too calculating.

487
00:18:47,494 --> 00:18:48,759
Deliberate.

488
00:18:48,761 --> 00:18:50,862
Until we find a link
       between these t--

489
00:18:50,864 --> 00:18:53,030
Teeny-tiny doughnuts,
      or cool ranch puffs?

490
00:18:53,032 --> 00:18:55,566
Lucifer, you can't
                 just steal food

491
00:18:55,568 --> 00:18:57,635
in the middle
                of the precinct.
Why?

492
00:18:57,637 --> 00:18:58,903
Are you gonna put me
on the naughty step,

493
00:18:58,905 --> 00:19:00,805
so I can have a think
about what I've done?

494
00:19:00,807 --> 00:19:02,540
(cell phone rings)

495
00:19:02,542 --> 00:19:04,609
Hey, Monkey.

496
00:19:04,611 --> 00:19:06,277
Yes, yeah, I-I'm
                   really sorry.

497
00:19:06,279 --> 00:19:08,279
Work got busy.

498
00:19:08,281 --> 00:19:10,915
Yes, I really, really want
  to take you trick-or-treating.

499
00:19:10,917 --> 00:19:13,151
But if Mommy or Daddy
     can't make it home in time,

500
00:19:13,153 --> 00:19:15,653
Babysitter Shelly might
    have to take you, okay?

501
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:17,388
Oh, she already left.

502
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:19,357
What? Why?
         I don't know.

503
00:19:19,359 --> 00:19:20,925
But when she went
       into Maze's room,

504
00:19:20,927 --> 00:19:22,927
she ran out screaming.

505
00:19:22,929 --> 00:19:24,529
It was hilarious.

506
00:19:24,531 --> 00:19:27,064
Who's watching you now?
             Maze.

507
00:19:27,066 --> 00:19:29,500
Can she take me
       trick-or-treating?

508
00:19:29,502 --> 00:19:30,935
No.
                  Mommy, please?

509
00:19:30,937 --> 00:19:32,770
I promise I'll be good.

510
00:19:32,772 --> 00:19:35,406
Yeah, babe, it's not you
    that I'm worried about.

511
00:19:35,408 --> 00:19:37,108
Please, please,
        please, please?

512
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:39,076
(huffs)

513
00:19:39,078 --> 00:19:40,745
All right,
     put Maze on the phone.

514
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:45,016
