00:29:29,635 --> 00:29:31,135
duh.

773
00:29:31,137 --> 00:29:34,338
President of Mars!

774
00:29:34,340 --> 00:29:35,539
All right.

775
00:29:35,541 --> 00:29:38,275
¶ Spirits rising
      from the ground... ¶

776
00:29:38,277 --> 00:29:40,577
¶ Out comes that spooky sound ¶

777
00:29:40,579 --> 00:29:44,314
¶ It's a haunted rave ¶

778
00:29:44,316 --> 00:29:46,817
¶<i> It's a haunted rave...</i> ¶

779
00:29:46,819 --> 00:29:48,152
(man chuckles)

780
00:29:49,288 --> 00:29:52,456
¶<i> Straight from the grave ¶</i>

781
00:29:52,458 --> 00:29:56,360
¶ And the dead will dance ¶

782
00:29:56,362 --> 00:29:57,761
¶<i> And the dead will</i> ¶

783
00:29:57,763 --> 00:30:01,098
¶<i> Dance</i> ¶

784
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:05,536
¶ You'd better run
 while you've got the chance. ¶

785
00:30:06,472 --> 00:30:08,138
Isn't this fun?

786
00:30:09,475 --> 00:30:11,708
I expected worse.

787
00:30:12,845 --> 00:30:13,844
(sighs)

788
00:30:13,846 --> 00:30:16,013
I wish you
wore a costume.

789
00:30:17,349 --> 00:30:19,616
Well, I, uh...

790
00:30:19,618 --> 00:30:22,686
I did bring something.

791
00:30:24,223 --> 00:30:25,856
Do you want to see it?

792
00:30:25,858 --> 00:30:26,957
Yeah.

793
00:30:28,327 --> 00:30:29,827
Turn around.

794
00:30:30,663 --> 00:30:32,963
(whooshing and low rumble)

795
00:30:32,965 --> 00:30:34,164
I'm ready.

796
00:30:39,471 --> 00:30:41,104
Cool!

797
00:30:41,106 --> 00:30:42,406
(exhales nervously)

798
00:30:42,408 --> 00:30:43,841
We're gonna get so much candy.

799
00:30:44,977 --> 00:30:46,777
(chuckles)

800
00:30:46,779 --> 00:30:48,979
(indistinct conversation)

801
00:31:04,763 --> 00:31:07,130
(piano key plays slowly)

802
00:31:08,667 --> 00:31:11,735
(playing
   Metallica's "Unforgiven")

803
00:31:23,148 --> 00:31:24,481
Why?

804
00:31:24,483 --> 00:31:25,515
Why did you bring me here?

805
00:31:25,517 --> 00:31:26,516
You have been

806
00:31:26,518 --> 00:31:28,685
so focused on blame...

807
00:31:28,687 --> 00:31:31,521
you haven't let yourself grieve.

808
00:31:31,523 --> 00:31:33,390
This isn't right.

809
00:31:33,392 --> 00:31:35,659
None of it.

810
00:31:35,661 --> 00:31:37,227
Why did he do this?

811
00:31:37,229 --> 00:31:38,295
Lucifer was just trying...

812
00:31:38,297 --> 00:31:39,396
No, Mom.

813
00:31:39,398 --> 00:31:41,765
Not Lucifer, Father.

814
00:31:44,470 --> 00:31:47,104
How did He let this happen?

815
00:31:47,106 --> 00:31:49,172
Son, it's okay.

816
00:31:49,708 --> 00:31:51,508
Just let it out.

817
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:54,912
Let it all... out.

818
00:31:57,850 --> 00:32:00,317
(continues playing
       "The Unforgiven")

819
00:32:13,299 --> 00:32:15,933
AMENADIEL:
   <i> I blame Father for this.</i>

820
00:32:15,935 --> 00:32:17,734
<i> You're right, Mom,</i>
         <i> where is he?</i>

821
00:32:17,736 --> 00:32:19,603
If he wanted to,
he could've prevented

822
00:32:19,605 --> 00:32:21,605
all of this from happening.

823
00:32:21,607 --> 00:32:25,208
All the misunderstandings,
all the pain.

824
00:32:26,211 --> 00:32:27,744
Well, I'm done.

825
00:32:27,746 --> 00:32:31,815
I'm done trying to please
someone who isn't ever here.

826
00:32:42,061 --> 00:32:44,027
¶ ¶

827
00:32:46,799 --> 00:32:49,099
(discordant notes)

828
00:32:57,276 --> 00:32:58,508
(panting)

829
00:32:58,510 --> 00:32:59,676
Out.

830
00:32:59,678 --> 00:33:02,245
All of you out! Go on!

831
00:33:02,247 --> 00:33:03,981
Go!

832
00:33:18,764 --> 00:33:20,931
¶ ¶

833
00:33:26,205 --> 00:33:27,404
CHLOE:
Anything connecting our shooter

834
00:33:27,406 --> 00:33:29,206
to Strode Pharmaceuticals?
          DAN: Yeah. Right here.

835
00:33:29,208 --> 00:33:31,908
Wes Williams' took part in one
 of their clinical drug trials.

836
00:33:31,910 --> 00:33:33,710
A "promising new treatment"
for her lung disease.

837
00:33:33,712 --> 00:33:35,078
Not promising enough
                    to save her.

838
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:37,080
No. Turns out she was
in the placebo group.

839
00:33:37,082 --> 00:33:39,082
Is that why he's pissed off?
              Who put her there?

840
00:33:39,084 --> 00:33:41,084
No one, really.
     It was a double-blind,

841
00:33:41,086 --> 00:33:43,453
so just like the doctor and the
lawyer, no one's at fault here.

842
00:33:43,455 --> 00:33:44,988
So who does our shooter
              think is at fault?

843
00:33:44,990 --> 00:33:46,223
Who ran the trials?

844
00:33:46,225 --> 00:33:48,058
Dr. Jack Peterson.

845
00:33:48,060 --> 00:33:49,860
And since Williams
     is targeting spouses,

846
00:33:49,862 --> 00:33:51,628
if we find Mrs. Peterson,
          assuming...

847
00:33:51,630 --> 00:33:53,130
No, wait... crap.
What?

848
00:33:53,132 --> 00:33:55,799
It also says that the trial was
  run by a Dr. Sally Peterson.

849
00:33:55,801 --> 00:33:57,267
They're a husband and wife team.

850
00:33:57,269 --> 00:33:58,935
Great. Who's the target?

851
00:33:58,937 --> 00:34:00,971
Well, it could be either one.
We got to get to both of them.

852
00:34:00,973 --> 00:34:02,739
Yeah, before he does.

853
00:34:04,443 --> 00:34:05,442
Dr. Peterson?

854
00:34:05,444 --> 00:34:06,576
LAPD.
Your wife, Sally.

855
00:34:06,578 --> 00:34:08,245
Where is she?
        What's going on?

856
00:34:08,247 --> 00:34:10,447
I'll explain later.
Where's your wife?

857
00:34:10,449 --> 00:34:11,448
Probably getting a coffee from

858
00:34:11,450 --> 00:34:12,449
the coffee cart
in the lobby.

859
00:34:12,451 --> 00:34:13,617
Okay, you stay with him.
         I'll find her.

860
00:34:13,619 --> 00:34:15,786
You be careful.
                          Right.

861
00:34:15,788 --> 00:34:16,787
You stay put.

862
00:34:16,789 --> 00:34:19,189
Here you go.
                Thank you.

863
00:34:26,298 --> 00:34:28,799
I know you're out there,
          Mr. Sniper!

864
00:34:37,342 --> 00:34:38,675
(gunshot)

865
00:34:38,677 --> 00:34:41,011
Oh, come on!

866
00:34:41,013 --> 00:34:43,747
LUCIFER:
  You can do better than that!

867
00:34:45,317 --> 00:34:46,450
(exhales)

868
00:34:46,452 --> 00:34:47,818
Shoot me!

869
00:34:53,025 --> 00:34:55,025
Well, go on, then!

870
00:34:55,027 --> 00:34:57,027
What are you waiting for?

871
00:34:57,029 --> 00:34:59,029
Just shoot me right now. Please!

872
00:34:59,031 --> 00:35:00,897
Lucifer, what are you doing?
Uh-oh!

873
00:35:00,899 --> 00:35:02,165
Police are here!

874
00:35:02,167 --> 00:35:04,501
Gonna have to hurry up,
       Mr. Shooter, sir.

875
00:35:05,771 --> 00:35:07,904
(screaming)

876
00:35:07,906 --> 00:35:10,373
Seriously? I mean,
    I'm standing right here.

877
00:35:16,181 --> 00:35:18,081
Right. You're just
  embarrassing yourself, now.

878
00:35:18,083 --> 00:35:20,484
I mean, could you be
      any worse of a shot?

879
00:35:23,922 --> 00:35:25,355
(gunshot)

880
00:35:26,058 --> 00:35:27,958
LUCIFER:
          Oh, come on.

881
00:35:30,696 --> 00:35:33,230
Che... It's like
     he's not even trying.

882
00:35:39,404 --> 00:35:41,671
Not her, you idiot-- me!

883
00:35:41,673 --> 00:35:43,140
Shoot me!

884
00:35:47,813 --> 00:35:50,013
Drop your weapon now.

885
00:35:59,791 --> 00:36:01,992
(distant sirens wailing)

886
00:36:06,565 --> 00:36:08,899
You.

887
00:36:08,901 --> 00:36:10,233
Why didn't you shoot me?

888
00:36:10,235 --> 00:36:12,235
Shoot you?
I was standing

889
00:36:12,237 --> 00:36:14,671
right here, fair game.
Why didn't you do it?

890
00:36:14,673 --> 00:36:16,072
Because you didn't
                     deserve it.

891
00:36:16,074 --> 00:36:18,408
How do you know what I deserve?

892
00:36:18,410 --> 00:36:20,777
I was trying to scare
              you away from her.

893
00:36:20,779 --> 00:36:22,412
I only wanted the people
            who killed Cassandra

894
00:36:22,414 --> 00:36:23,413
to suffer like...

895
00:36:23,415 --> 00:36:24,581
What...?

896
00:36:24,583 --> 00:36:27,417
Like I'm suffering.

897
00:36:27,419 --> 00:36:28,852
You idiot!

898
00:36:28,854 --> 00:36:30,253
Lucifer.
The doctor,

899
00:36:30,255 --> 00:36:32,122
the lawyer, that woman--
they didn't kill your wife!

900
00:36:32,124 --> 00:36:33,857
They aren't responsible!

901
00:36:34,693 --> 00:36:36,293
But you know that.

902
00:36:36,295 --> 00:36:39,829
You hold someone else
accountable, don't you?

903
00:36:39,831 --> 00:36:43,967
If I hadn't been
     on mission so long...

904
00:36:43,969 --> 00:36:46,803
Been home when
     Cassandra needed me...

905
00:36:46,805 --> 00:36:48,972
we could've detected it sooner.

906
00:36:48,974 --> 00:36:52,209
She would still be alive.

907
00:36:52,211 --> 00:36:54,077
Yes.

908
00:36:54,079 --> 00:36:56,346
So it's not vengeance you want.

909
00:36:56,348 --> 00:36:57,647
It's punishment.

910
00:37:02,588 --> 00:37:04,888
Well, now you've got it.

911
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:06,623
Good for you.

912
00:37:13,365 --> 00:37:14,431
I got this.

913
00:37:16,902 --> 00:37:18,335
Hey.

914
00:37:21,006 --> 00:37:22,305
How did you find us?

915
00:37:22,307 --> 00:37:24,007
Just called the station chief.

916
00:37:24,009 --> 00:37:25,508
Got all the details.

917
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:28,845
What you just did was
  extremely reckless and stupid.

918
00:37:28,847 --> 00:37:29,913
(scoffs)

919
00:37:29,915 --> 00:37:31,581
But you saved
              that woman's life.

920
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:34,317
I couldn't care less
about that woman's life.

921
00:37:34,319 --> 00:37:37,387
So, what, you were just trying
         to get yourself killed?

922
00:37:38,390 --> 00:37:39,689
No.

923
00:37:39,691 --> 00:37:40,857
I don't buy it.

924
00:37:40,859 --> 00:37:43,093
Every time you say
            that you don't care,

925
00:37:43,095 --> 00:37:45,328
or that you're evil,
            or you're the Devil,

926
00:37:45,330 --> 00:37:47,597
I know that's not
             who you really are.

927
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:49,966
You don't know a thing
about who I am, Detective.

928
00:37:49,968 --> 00:37:51,334
Or what I've done.

929
00:37:51,336 --> 00:37:54,938
You weren't just talking about
       Wes back there, were you?

930
00:37:56,975 --> 00:37:58,975
You want to be punished
                  for something.

931
00:37:58,977 --> 00:38:01,077
That's why you've been
            acting out recently.

932
00:38:01,079 --> 00:38:04,114
Just talk to me,
                Lucifer, please.

933
00:38:04,116 --> 00:38:06,683
Just tell me what's going on.

934
00:38:06,685 --> 00:38:09,085
I'm here for you, okay? I...

935
00:38:10,722 --> 00:38:13,123
I just want to understand.

936
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:17,560
You can't understand, Detective.

937
00:38:19,731 --> 00:38:22,465
And you never will.

938
00:38:22,467 --> 00:38:27,137
Well, if you won't
             talk to me, then...

939
00:38:27,139 --> 00:38:29,839
please, talk to someone else.

940
00:38:29,841 --> 00:38:32,409
You have a therapist.

941
00:38:32,411 --> 00:38:35,979
Talk to her,
   before it eats you alive.

942
00:38:35,981 --> 00:38:39,316
¶ ¶

943
00:38:49,227 --> 00:38:51,428
(strange noises on TV)

944
00:38:54,299 --> 00:38:56,066
(gasps)

945
00:38:56,902 --> 00:38:59,736
MAN:
             Now...

946
00:38:59,738 --> 00:39:01,738
(cackles)

947
00:39:04,710 --> 00:39:06,042
(creature squeaking)

948
00:39:11,616 --> 00:39:13,016
(woman screams)

949
00:39:13,018 --> 00:39:15,218
¶ ¶

950
00:39:19,124 --> 00:39:22,125
I'm glad you
              changed your mind.

951
00:39:25,197 --> 00:39:28,431
Are you ready to talk
      about your brother?

952
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:35,004
His name is...

953
00:39:35,006 --> 00:39:38,375
<i> was</i> Uriel.

954
00:39:39,177 --> 00:39:41,678
And ever since he died,

955
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:44,214
I've been having this...
        strange feeling.

956
00:39:44,216 --> 00:39:47,884
Something I've never
          felt before.

957
00:39:47,886 --> 00:39:49,786
Guilt.

958
00:39:50,822 --> 00:39:54,224
Why do you feel guilty?

959
00:39:57,329 --> 00:39:59,529
Uriel didn't just die.

960
00:40:00,932 --> 00:40:02,899
I killed him.

961
00:40:02,901 --> 00:40:04,734
I've never...

962
00:40:04,736 --> 00:40:07,704
killed anyone before. Only
punished those already dead.

963
00:40:07,706 --> 00:40:11,674
You know, back when
I used to run Hell.

964
00:40:11,676 --> 00:40:13,209
But...
(drinks)

965
00:40:13,211 --> 00:40:16,346
A stubborn Uriel...
he-he gave me no choice.

966
00:40:16,348 --> 00:40:18,481
He came down
from the Silver City

967
00:40:18,483 --> 00:40:20,550
to collect on the deal
     that I made with Dad.

968
00:40:20,552 --> 00:40:24,387
Intent on killing the detective
or smiting Mum out of existence.

969
00:40:24,389 --> 00:40:26,356
Lucifer...
He brought Azrael's
blade with him,

970
00:40:26,358 --> 00:40:28,358
which is a... a divine dagger
    that destroys your soul,

971
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:29,759
it doesn't just kill you.

972
00:40:29,761 --> 00:40:31,761
It... wipes you out...
                Lucifer, enough.

973
00:40:32,798 --> 00:40:33,863
(exhales)

974
00:40:35,233 --> 00:40:37,434
I can't do this anymore.

975
00:40:38,904 --> 00:40:41,871
I can't keep track of all these
      elaborate metaphors.

976
00:40:41,873 --> 00:40:43,706
But it's not a metaphor,

977
00:40:43,708 --> 00:40:45,175
Doctor.

978
00:40:45,177 --> 00:40:46,609
You need to take me seriously.

979
00:40:46,611 --> 00:40:49,112
You need to believe
        what I'm saying.

980
00:40:49,114 --> 00:40:51,314
Otherwise, you'll
never understand...

981
00:40:52,984 --> 00:40:55,518
I'm a monster.

982
00:40:55,520 --> 00:40:58,321
A monster who...
    deserves to be punished.

983
00:40:58,323 --> 00:41:00,757
I believe you
                  feel that way.

984
00:41:00,759 --> 00:41:01,991
(sighs)

985
00:41:01,993 --> 00:41:03,960
And I want
                  to understand.

986
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:05,628
I truly do!

987
00:41:05,630 --> 00:41:07,530
But, Lucifer,
      you have to help me.

988
00:41:07,532 --> 00:41:10,033
I need you to be
                 honest with me.

989
00:41:10,035 --> 00:41:12,602
Completely honest...

990
00:41:14,005 --> 00:41:16,139
...about who you are.

991
00:41:16,141 --> 00:41:18,908
Completely honest?

992
00:41:18,910 --> 00:41:20,243
Are you sure?
                            Yes.

993
00:41:20,245 --> 00:41:22,545
Yes, I'm sure.

994
00:41:22,547 --> 00:41:25,148
That's what all
             of these sessions--

995
00:41:25,150 --> 00:41:28,284
our entire relationship--
         is all about.

996
00:41:28,286 --> 00:41:31,921
Getting to know
               the<i> real</i> Lucifer.

997
00:41:31,923 --> 00:41:33,890
(exhales)

998
00:41:33,892 --> 00:41:35,792
No more lies.

999
00:41:35,794 --> 00:41:37,927
No more metaphors.

1000
00:41:37,929 --> 00:41:40,029
Very well.

1001
00:41:40,031 --> 00:41:42,232
¶ ¶

1002
00:41:47,739 --> 00:41:50,740
¶ ¶

1003
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:04,521
(quietly):
             Yes...

1004
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:07,857
Doctor?

1005
00:42:13,698 --> 00:42:14,764
Uh...

1006
00:42:42,561 --> 00:42:43,626
(gasps)

